  <prompt>
    Run `npm run build` (NOT `npm run build:prod` — type-check + bundle check only; this is not a deploy) for `Spaarke.AI.Widgets` shared lib and the `SpaarkeAi` code page solution to confirm the ADR-030 v2 type extension compiles end-to-end and bundles without error.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform frontend developer running build gate.</role>

  <goal>
    Both packages build successfully. Build artifacts produced; no bundler / Vite errors. Confirms additive type extension is buildable in addition to type-checkable.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Wave 4-A2 final gate before Phase 4b (upload pipeline services) begins. Cross-wave: task 103 (Phase 4 integration test suite) depends on this build verification because the integration tests exercise the frontend memory subscriber path. Task 062 type-checked; this task confirms full build (bundler resolves all imports, tree-shake doesn't break anything, etc.).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/package.json</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/package.json</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md">Use `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` (NOT `npm ci`) for Vite solutions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Use `npm run build` for type-check + bundle verification (NOT `npm run build:prod` — that's for deployment).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
